JOHANNESBURG - Forensic pathology officers say they re ready to go back to work as soon as government meets their demands. The parties are making headway with their negotiations.But the deadlock persists around recognition of post-mortem work, and an allowance for dissecting bodies.READ: Gauteng mortuary strike continuesThe officers insist they're not on strike.They re simply refusing to do out-of-scope work, which includes dissecting bodies.This is what's slowed processes at Gauteng's mortuaries. eNCA